%U A397743 6306411043525632000,530946503562997987500,47876129916092928000000,4603521212261405490225000,470209485165582143631360000,50843713447609660550744718750
%N A397743 Number of assembly trees for the n-sunlet graph.
%C A397743 The n-sunlet graph is properly defined for n >= 3. For n = 1 and 2 a loop or double edge with pendent vertices is used.
%H A397743 Andrew Howroyd, <a href="/A397743/b397743.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..200</a>
%H A397743 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/AssemblyNumber.html">Assembly Number</a>.
%H A397743 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/SunletGraph.html">Sunlet Graph</a>.
%F A397743 a(n) = n*A062980(n-1)/2 for n > 1.
%o A397743 (PARI) seq(n) = { my(v=vector(n)); v[1] = 2; v[2] = 5; for(n=3, n, v[n] = 6*(n-1)*v[n-1] + sum(k=2,n-2,v[k]*v[n-k])); vector(#v,n,v[n]*n)/2 }
%Y A397743 Cf. A062980 (for centipede graph).
%K A397743 nonn,new
%O A397743 1,2
%A A397743 _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 08 2026
